thread.title: Nebraska national champion Tyus Wilson named Big Ten men's field athlete of year
thread.title_full: Nebraska national champion Tyus Wilson named Big Ten men's field athlete of year

author: From Staff Reports
title: Nebraska national champion Tyus Wilson named Big Ten men's field athlete of year
text:
Fresh off a national title, Nebraska track athlete Tyus Wilson has a new award with his name inscribed on it.
That's the Big Ten men's field athlete of the year honor, which the conference awarded to Wilson days after the Husker senior struck gold in the high jump at the NCAA Championships on Saturday in Virginia Beach, Virginia.
Wilson became NU's first male indoor champion since 2009 when he jumped 7 feet, 3/4 inches, setting a new personal record and the third-highest mark in school history.
Wilson becomes the fourth consecutive Husker to earn the honor.
